<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(b) The specific referral requirements of this part are limited to known or suspected criminal violations of the United
States Code involving the assets, operations, or affairs of an institution. This part prescribes procedures for
referring those violations to the proper Federal authorities and the Farm Credit Administration. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) Nothing in this part should be construed as reducing in any way an institution's responsibility to report known
or suspected criminal activities to the appropriate investigatory or prosecuting authorities, whether State or
Federal, even if circumstances required for a report under &sect;617.2 are not present. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(d) Each referral required by &sect;617.2(a) shall be made on the Referral Form in accordance with the Referral Form
Instructions relating to its filing and distribution and the requirements of &sect;617.2 (b) and (c). 
