227.403&hyph;11
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Contractor procedures and records.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) The clause at 252.227&hyph;7013, ``Rights in Technical Data_Noncommercial Items'', requires a contractor,
and its subcontractors or suppliers that will deliver technical data with other than unlimited rights, to establish
and follow written procedures to assure that restrictive markings are used only when authorized and to maintain records
to justify the validity of asserted restrictions on delivered data.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) The clause at 252.227&hyph;7037, ``Validation of Asserted Restrictions'', requires contractors and their
subcontractors at any tier to maintain records sufficient to justify the validity of restrictive markings on technical
data delivered or to be delivered under a Government contract.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
227.403&hyph;12
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Government right to establish conformity of markings.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Nonconforming markings.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 (1) Authorized markings are identified in the clause at 252.227&hyph;7013, ``Rights in Technical Data.'' All other
markings are nonconforming markings. An authorized marking that is not in the form, or differs in substance, from
the marking requirements in the clause at 252.227&hyph;7013 is also a nonconforming marking.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) The correction of nonconforming markings on technical data is not subject to 252.227&hyph;7037, ``Validation
of Asserted Restrictions''. To the extent practicable, the contracting officer should return technical data bearing
nonconforming markings to the person who has placed the nonconforming markings on such data to provide that person
an opportunity to correct or strike the nonconforming marking at that person's expense. If the person who has placed
the nonconforming marking on the technical data fails to correct the nonconformity and return the corrected data
within 60 days following the person's receipt of the data, the contracting officer may correct or strike the nonconformity
at that person's expense. When it is impracticable to return technical data for correction, contracting officers
may unilaterally correct any nonconforming markings at Government expense. Prior to correction of the nonconformity,
the data may be used in accordance with the proper restrictive marking.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Unjustified markings.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 (1) An unjustified marking is an authorized marking that does not depict accurately restrictions applicable to the
Government's use, modification, reproduction, release, performance, display, or disclosure of the marked technical
data. For example, a limited rights legend placed on technical data pertaining to items, components, or processes
that were developed under a Government contract either exclusively at Government expense or with mixed funding (situations
under which the Government obtains unlimited or government purpose rights) is an unjustified marking.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Contracting officers have the right to review and challenge the validity of unjustified markings. However, at
any time during performance of a contract and notwithstanding the existence of a challenge, the contracting officer
and the person who has asserted a restrictive marking may agree that the restrictive marking is not justified. Upon
such agreement, the contracting officer may, at his or her election, either_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Strike or correct the unjustified marking at that person's expense; or, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Return the technical data to the person asserting the restriction for correction at that person's expense. If
the data are returned and that person fails to correct or strike the unjustified restriction and return the corrected
data to the contracting officer within sixty (60) days following receipt of the data, the unjustified marking shall
be corrected or stricken at that person's expense.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
227.403&hyph;13
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Government right to review, verify, challenge and validate asserted restrictions.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
General.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 An offeror's assertion(s) of restrictions on the Government's rights to use, modify, reproduce, release, or disclose
technical data do not, by themselves, determine the extent of the Government's rights in the technical data. Under
10 U.S.C. 2321, the Government has the right to challenge asserted restrictions when there are reasonable grounds
to question the validity of the assertion and continued adherence to the assertion would make it impractical to later
procure competitively the item to which the data pertain.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Pre-award considerations.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 The challenge procedures required by 10 U.S.C. 2321 could significantly delay awards under competitive procurements.
Therefore, avoid challenging asserted restrictions prior to a competitive contract award unless resolution of
the assertion is essential for successful completion of the procurement.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Challenge and validation.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 Contracting officers must have reasonable grounds to challenge the current validity of an asserted restriction.
Before issuing a challenge to an asserted restriction, carefully consider all available information pertaining
to the assertion. All challenges must be made in accordance with the provisions of the clause at 252.227&hyph;7037,
``Validation of Asserted Restrictions''.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Challenge period. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Asserted restrictions should be reviewed before acceptance of technical data deliverable under the contract. Assertions
must be challenged within 3 years after final payment under the contract or three years after delivery of the data,
whichever is later. However, restrictive markings may be challenged at any time if the technical data_
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
