<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(i) Are publicly available without restrictions;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Have been provided to the United States without restriction; or,
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) Have been otherwise made available without restriction other than a release or disclosure resulting from the
sale, transfer, or other assignment of interest in the software to another party or the sale or transfer of some or all
of a business entity or its assets to another party.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Pre-challenge requests for information.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 (i) After consideration of the situations described in 227.403&hyph;13(c)(3), contracting officers may request
the person asserting a restriction to furnish a written explanation of the facts and supporting documentation for
the assertion in sufficient detail to enable the contracting officer to determine the validity of the assertion.
Additional supporting documentation may be requested when the explanation provided by the person making the assertion
does not, in the contracting officer's opinion, establish the validity of the assertion.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) If the person asserting the restriction fails to respond to the contracting officer's request for information
or additional supporting documentation or if the information submitted does not justify the asserted restriction,
a challenge should be considered.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Transacting matters directly with subcontractors.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 The clause at 252.227&hyph;7037 obtains the contractor's agreement that the Government may transact matters under
the clause directly with a subcontractor, at any tier, without creating or implying privity of contract. Contracting
officers should permit a subcontractor or supplier to transact challenge and validation matters directly with the
Government when_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) A subcontractor's or supplier's business interests in its technical data would be compromised if the data were
disclosed to a higher tier contractor; or,
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) There is reason to believe that the contractor will not respond in a timely manner to a challenge and a failure to
respond would jeopardize a subcontractor's or supplier's right to assert restrictions; or,
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) Requested to do so by a subcontractor or supplier.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Challenge notice.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 Do not issue a challenge notice unless there are reasonable grounds to question the validity of an assertion. Assertions
may be challenged whether or not supporting documentation was requested from the person asserting the restriction.
Challenge notices must be in writing and issued to the contractor or, after consideration of the situations described
in 227.403&hyph;13(c)(3), the person asserting the restriction. The challenge notice must include the information
in paragraph (d) of the clause at 252.227&hyph;7037, ``Validation of Asserted Restrictions.''
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Extension of response time.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 The contracting officer, at his or her discretion, may extend the time for response contained in a challenge notice,
as appropriate, if the contractor submits a timely written request showing the need for additional time to prepare
a response.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(6) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Contracting officer's final decision.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 Contracting officers must issue a final decision for each challenged assertion, whether or not the assertion has
been justified.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) A contracting officer's final decision that an assertion is not justified must be issued as soon as practicable
following the failure of the person asserting the restriction to respond to the contracting officer's challenge
within sixty (60) days, or any extension to that time granted by the contracting officer.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) A contracting officer who, following a challenge and response by the person asserting the restriction, determines
that an asserted restriction is justified, shall issue a final decision sustaining the validity of the asserted restriction.
If the asserted restriction was made subsequent to submission of the contractor's offer, add the asserted restriction
to the contract Attachment.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) A contracting officer who determines that the validity of an asserted restriction has not been justified shall
issue a contracting officer's final decision within the time frames prescribed in 252.227&hyph;7037, ``Validation
of Asserted Restrictions.'' As provided in paragraph (f) of that clause, the Government is obligated to continue
to respect the asserted restrictions through final disposition of any appeal unless the Agency Head notifies the
person asserting the restriction that urgent or compelling circumstances do not permit the Government to continue
to respect the asserted restriction.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(7) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Multiple challenges to an asserted restriction.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 When more than one contracting officer challenges an asserted restriction, the contracting officer who made the
earliest challenge is responsible for coordinating the Government challenges. That contracting officer shall
consult with all other contracting officers making challenges, verify that all challenges apply to the same asserted
restriction and, after consulting with the contractor, subcontractor, or supplier asserting the restriction,
issue a schedule that provides that person a reasonable opportunity to respond to each challenge.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
