<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;227.405&hyph;2
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Acquisition of existing works without modification.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) Use the clause at 252.227&hyph;7021, ``Rights in Data_Existing Works'' in lieu of the clause at 252.227&hyph;7013,
``Rights in Technical Data_Noncommercial Items'', in solicitations and contracts exclusively for existing works
when:
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) The existing works will be acquired without modification; and,
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) The Government requires the right to reproduce, prepare derivative works, or publicly perform or display the
existing works; or,
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) The Government has a specific need to obtain indemnity for liabilities that may arise out of the content, performance,
use, or disclosure of such data.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) The clause at 252.227&hyph;7021, ``Rights in Data_Existing Works'', provides the Government, and others acting
on its behalf, a paid-up, non-exclusive, irrevocable, worldwide license to reproduce, prepare derivative works
and publicly perform or display the works called for by a contract and to authorize others to do so for Government purposes.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) A contract clause is not required to acquire existing works such as books, magazines and periodicals in any storage
or retrieval medium, when the Government will not reproduce the books, magazines or periodicals, or prepare derivative
works.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;227.405&hyph;3
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Acquisition of modified existing works.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Use the clause at 252.227&hyph;7020, ``Rights in Data_Special Works'', in solicitations and contracts for modified
existing works in lieu of the clause at 252.227&hyph;7021, ``Rights in Data_Existing Works.''
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;227.406
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Contracts for special works.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) Use the clause at 252.227&hyph;7020, ``Rights in Special Works'' in solicitations and contracts where the Government
has a specific need to control the distribution of works first produced, created, or generated in the performance
of a contract and required to be delivered under that contract, including controlling distribution by obtaining
an assignment of copyright, or a specific need to obtain indemnity for liabilities that may arise out of the content,
performance, use, or disclosure of such works. Use the clause_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) In lieu of the clause at 252.227&hyph;7013, ``Rights in Technical Data_Noncommercial Items'', when the Government
must own or control copyright in all works first produced, created, or generated and required to be delivered under
a contract.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) In addition to the clause at 252.227&hyph;7013, ``Rights in Technical Data_Noncommercial Items'' when the Government
must own or control copyright in a portion of a work first produced, created, or generated and required to be delivered
under a contract. The specific portion in which the Government must own or control copyright must be identified in
a special contract requirement.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) Although the Government obtains an assignment of copyright and unlimited rights in a special work under the clause
at 252.227&hyph;7020, the contractor retains use and disclosure rights in that work. If the Government needs to restrict
a contractor's rights to use or disclose a special work, it must also negotiate a special license which specifically
restricts the contractor's use or disclosure rights.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) The clause at 252.227&hyph;7020 does not permit a contractor to incorporate into a special work any works copyrighted
by others unless the contractor obtains the contracting officer's permission to do so and obtains for the Government
a non-exclusive, paid up, world-wide license to make and distribute copies of that work, to prepare derivative works,
to perform or display publicly any portion of the work, and to permit others to do so for government purposes. Grant
permission only when the Government's requirements cannot be satisfied unless the third party work is included in
the deliverable work.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
