<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(d) Examples of works which may be procured under the ``Rights in Special Works'' clause include, but are not limited,
to audiovisual works, computer data bases, computer software documentation, scripts, soundtracks, musical compositions,
and adaptations; histories of departments, agencies, services or units thereof; surveys of Government establishments;
instructional works or guidance to Government officers and employees on the discharge of their official duties;
reports, books, studies, surveys or similar documents; collections of data containing information pertaining
to individuals that, if disclosed, would violate the right of privacy or publicity of the individuals to whom the information
relates; or, investigative reports.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
227.407
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Contracts for architect-engineer services.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
This section sets forth policies and procedures, pertaining to data, copyrights, and restricted designs unique
to the acquisition of construction and architect-engineer services.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
227.407&hyph;1
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Architectural designs and data clauses for architect-engineer or construction contracts.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) Except as provided in 227.407&hyph;1(b), use the clause at 252.227&hyph;7022, ``Government Rights (Unlimited)'',
in solicitations and contracts for architect-engineer services and for construction involving architect-engineer
services.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) When the purpose of a contract for architect-engineer services or for construction involving architect-engineer
services is to obtain a unique architectural design of a building, a monument, or construction of similar nature,
which for artistic, aesthetic or other special reasons the Government does not want duplicated, the Government may
acquire exclusive control of the data pertaining to the design by including the clause at 252.227&hyph;7023, ``Drawings
and Other Data to Become Property of Government'', in solicitations and contracts.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) The Government shall obtain unlimited rights in shop drawings for construction. In solicitations and contracts
calling for delivery of shop drawings, include the clause at 252.227&hyph;7033, Rights in Shop Drawings.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
227.407&hyph;2
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Contracts for construction supplies and research and development work.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The provisions and clauses required by 227.407&hyph;1 shall not be used when the acquisition is limited to_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(a) Construction supplies or materials;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) Experimental, developmental, or research work, or test and evaluation studies of structures, equipment, processes,
or materials for use in construction; or,
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) Both.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
227.407&hyph;3
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Approval of restricted designs.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The clause at 252.227&hyph;7024, ``Notice and Approval of Restricted Designs'', may be included in architect-engineer
contracts to permit the Government to make informed decisions concerning noncompetitive aspects of the design.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
227.408
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Contractor data repositories.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) Contractor data repositories may be established when permitted by agency procedures. The contractual instrument
establishing the data repository must require, as a minimum, the data repository management contractor to_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Establish and maintain adequate procedures for protecting technical data delivered to or stored at the repository
from unauthorized release or disclosure;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Establish and maintain adequate procedures for controlling the release or disclosure of technical data from
the repository to third parties consistent with the Government's rights in such data;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) When required by the contracting officer, deliver data to the Government on paper or in other specified media;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) Be responsible for maintaining the currency of data delivered directly by Government contractors or subcontractors
to the repository;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
